            Rules</docTitle><enactingFormula role="empoweringSection">(<ref href="/hk/cap132/s117">Cap. 132, section
                117</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></enactingFormula><commencementNote>[20 April 1961]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="/hk/2012/er2">E.R. 2 of 2012</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438402669827_001" name="s1" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Citation</heading><content>These rules may be cited as the Hong Kong Cemetery, Happy Valley, Rules. </content><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1977/ln288">L.N. 288 of 1977</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438402669827_003" name="s2" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Hours of opening and closing</heading><content>The Hong Kong Cemetery, Happy Valley, shall be open to the public at the following times—</content><content class="first_line_indent_-24 left_indent_84">1 April to 30 September - 7 a.m. to 7 p.m. </content><content class="first_line_indent_-24 left_indent_84">1 October to 31 March - 7 a.m. to 6 p.m. <marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></content></section><section id="ID_1438402669843_002" name="s3" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Animals</heading><content>No person shall permit any dog or other animal to enter the cemetery.<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></content></section><section id="ID_1438402669859_001" name="s4" reason="inEffect" role="rule" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Bands and photographs</heading><leadIn>Except with the prior permission of the Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene—  <sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1999/78">78 of 1999 s. 7</ref>)</sourceNote></leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438411186737_012" name="a" temporalId="s4_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>no band may enter or play within the cemetery; and<inline class="width_5"> </inline><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/2012/2">2 of 2012 s. 3</ref>)</sourceNote></content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438411186737_020" name="b" temporalId="s4_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>no person may take any photograph in the cemetery of any process of burial or
                of any religious or other ceremony conducted in
                connexion
                therewith.</content></paragraph></section></main></subLeg>